quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  18,1,"All praise unto Allah who hath sent down unto His bondman the Book, and hath not placed therein any crookedness"
  18,2,"Straightforward, that it may warn of a severe violence from before Him, and bring glad tidings to the believers who work righteous works that theirs shall be a goodly hire"
  18,3,They will abide therein for ever
  18,4,"And that it may warn those who say: God hath taken a son"
  18,5,"No knowledge thereof have they, nor had their fathers. Odious is the word that cometh out of their mouths; they say not but a lie"
  18,6,"Haply thou art going to kill thyself over their footsteps, if they believe not in this discourse, out of sorrow"
  18,7,"Verily We have made whatsoever is on the earth as an adornment thereof, that We may prove them - which of them is best in work"
  18,8,And verily We are going to make whatsoever is thereon a soil bare
  18,9,Deemest thou that the people of the cave and the inscription were of Our signs a wonder
  18,10,"Recall what time the youths betook themselves to the cave, then said: our Lord! vouchsafe unto us mercy from before Thee, and prepare for us in our affair a right course"
  18,11,Wherefore We put a covering over their ears in the cave for a number of years
  18,12,Thereafter We raised them up that We might know which of the two parties was best at reckoning the time that they had tarried